00:54:12,582 --> 00:54:13,500
And also,

784
00:54:14,960 --> 00:54:17,379
I keep wanting to know more about you.

785
00:54:18,755 --> 00:54:19,839
Like what?

786
00:54:21,925 --> 00:54:23,176
It's nothing much.

787
00:54:25,303 --> 00:54:26,763
"What does Soo-bin

788
00:54:28,056 --> 00:54:29,975
look like when she sneezes?

789
00:54:30,934 --> 00:54:34,604
Does Soo-bin sleep
with her knees curled up?

790
00:54:34,729 --> 00:54:36,356
Does she lie on her side?

791
00:54:36,731 --> 00:54:38,191
Or does she raise her arms?"

792
00:54:41,194 --> 00:54:42,529
And also...

793
00:54:43,196 --> 00:54:45,073
I thought of things like that too.

794
00:54:46,950 --> 00:54:51,579
"Does Jun-u really have trouble
sleeping with the lights off?"

795
00:54:53,289 --> 00:54:55,417
I guess you can sleep
with the lights off lately

796
00:54:55,500 --> 00:54:56,668
since your mom's with you.

797
00:54:57,502 --> 00:54:58,628
Also...

798
00:54:59,504 --> 00:55:01,965
"When Jun-u smiles,

799
00:55:02,048 --> 00:55:04,634
does he know that his left eye
gets smaller?"

800
00:55:05,510 --> 00:55:06,594
It does?

801
00:55:07,721 --> 00:55:09,639
-No, it doesn't.
-It does.

802
00:55:10,598 --> 00:55:12,058
Try smiling properly.

803
00:55:13,059 --> 00:55:15,645
Hey. You're squinting your right eye

804
00:55:15,729 --> 00:55:17,313
on purpose, aren't you?

805
00:55:17,397 --> 00:55:18,940
-On purpose.
-No, I'm not.

806
00:55:19,024 --> 00:55:21,026
Who smiles like that?

807
00:55:21,609 --> 00:55:22,694
Open them properly.

808
00:55:22,777 --> 00:55:24,738
What are you doing?

809
00:55:34,414 --> 00:55:35,832
And when I'm with you,

810
00:55:36,583 --> 00:55:38,001
everything feels comfortable.

811
00:55:39,377 --> 00:55:41,838
Like all the troubles in this world
have disappeared.

812
00:55:45,050 --> 00:55:46,426
It's so hot.

813
00:55:47,427 --> 00:55:49,012
On days like this,
after washing your hair,

814
00:55:49,095 --> 00:55:52,307
if you stick your head outside
the window, it feels so refreshing.

815
00:55:53,767 --> 00:55:56,352
The cold breeze blows through your hair,

816
00:55:56,603 --> 00:55:58,271
and it feels like someone is blowing.

817
00:56:02,317 --> 00:56:05,153
It must feel like someone is
stroking your hair.

818
00:56:07,697 --> 00:56:08,698
Right.

819
00:56:10,784 --> 00:56:13,578
But you can't do it in winter.

820
00:56:15,497 --> 00:56:17,332
Your hair will freeze.

821
00:56:18,291 --> 00:56:20,460
You know, like when it's been hit
by lightning.

822
00:56:21,544 --> 00:56:22,879
I do get taller.

823
00:56:24,297 --> 00:56:25,507
But it doesn't work in winter.

824
00:56:25,632 --> 00:56:28,551
Of course not.
That's not your real height.

825
00:56:30,345 --> 00:56:31,387
I know.

826
00:56:35,475 --> 00:56:38,144
By the way, isn't it about time

827
00:56:38,228 --> 00:56:40,480
that you need to go to work?

828
00:56:41,356 --> 00:56:42,816
I still have 30 minutes left.

829
00:56:43,149 --> 00:56:44,400
Shall I walk you to the store?

830
00:56:46,277 --> 00:56:47,278
Sure.

831
00:56:48,279 --> 00:56:52,033
Then let me stop by my house
for a second before we go.

832
00:56:52,117 --> 00:56:53,159
Okay.

833
00:57:03,002 --> 00:57:04,170
Why am I hiccupping suddenly?

834
00:57:22,939 --> 00:57:23,982
Did I surprise you?

835
00:57:25,233 --> 00:57:26,234
Yes.

836
00:57:27,026 --> 00:57:28,027
Let's go.

837
00:57:33,074 --> 00:57:34,868
Wait, I left my phone at home.

838
00:57:34,951 --> 00:57:36,494
My mom said she'd call later.

839
00:57:36,953 --> 00:57:39,247
You're so clumsy. Go get it.

840
00:57:39,873 --> 00:57:40,874
I'll be right back.

841
00:57:46,337 --> 00:57:47,505
Are you okay?

842
00:57:48,047 --> 00:57:49,757
Yes, I'm fine. It'll stop soon.

843
00:57:56,931 --> 00:57:59,559
Why don't you come inside for some water?

844
00:58:01,186 --> 00:58:03,188
It's okay. It'll probably stop.

845
00:58:04,898 --> 00:58:06,900
Don't worry. My mom is at work now.

846
00:58:06,983 --> 00:58:08,026
We talked on the phone.

847
00:58:08,776 --> 00:58:09,903
Come inside for some water.

848
00:58:30,423 --> 00:58:32,342
Come on in. Get some water.

849
00:58:34,219 --> 00:58:35,428
Just get me a cup of water.

850
00:58:36,638 --> 00:58:38,598
No one's here. It's okay.

851
00:58:42,101 --> 00:58:43,186
All right, fine.

852
00:58:50,485 --> 00:58:52,403
-Here.
-Thanks.

853
00:58:59,369 --> 00:59:00,370
What are you doing?

854
00:59:02,956 --> 00:59:04,207
This gets rid of hiccups.

855
00:59:04,874 --> 00:59:06,668
I see. So has it stopped?

856
00:59:07,460 --> 00:59:08,962
-Yes.
-Nice.

857
00:59:09,921 --> 00:59:12,382
Have some more water.
I'll go get my phone.

858
00:59:15,510 --> 00:59:18,012
Hey! Hey, hurry.

859
00:59:19,305 --> 00:59:20,348
Come over here!

860
00:59:45,373 --> 00:59:48,167
Oh, it must be our housekeeper.

861
01:00:00,888 --> 01:00:04,350
It's okay. It's all good. We're okay now.

862
01:00:09,981 --> 01:00:11,065
Jun-u.

863
01:00:13,901 --> 01:00:14,861
Mom.

864
01:00:42,096 --> 01:00:44,182
By the way, what happened, Mom?

865
01:00:46,142 --> 01:00:47,769
Are you uncomfortable with it?

866
01:00:47,852 --> 01:00:50,438
I'm fine if you're okay with it.

867
01:00:50,521 --> 01:00:51,939
Someone posted something strange.

868
01:00:52,023 --> 01:00:53,816
The rumors about rigged grades
aren't true, right?

869
01:00:53,900 --> 01:00:54,901
What do you guys think?

870
01:00:54,984 --> 01:00:55,985
I trust you.

871
01:00:56,069 --> 01:00:58,363
Even if something unexpected did happen,

872
01:00:58,446 --> 01:01:01,658
I'm sure you wouldn't have
anything to do with it.

873
01:01:01,741 --> 01:01:02,784
Aren't I right?

874
01:01:02,867 --> 01:01:04,202
You understand everything, right?

875
01:01:04,285 --> 01:01:05,745
No, Dad.

876
01:01:05,828 --> 01:01:07,830
I just acted mature, that's all.

877
01:01:08,623 --> 01:01:09,957
I had to react that way

878
01:01:10,833 --> 01:01:12,752
to make it easier for you and Mom.

879
01:01:13,044 --> 01:01:15,338
Something must've upset you
when you met your dad earlier.

880
01:01:15,421 --> 01:01:17,924
What is the one thing you regret
the most in your life?

881
01:01:18,007 --> 01:01:19,634
Not being able to tell him that it was me.

882
01:01:19,717 --> 01:01:21,469
Let's go there again and tell him.

883
01:01:21,552 --> 01:01:24,222
I hope all your regrets are gone now.

884
01:01:24,305 --> 01:01:25,473
It's not your fault.

885
01:01:25,556 --> 01:01:27,767
You didn't know back then.

886
01:01:27,934 --> 01:01:29,644
You thought that was for the best then.

887
01:01:30,978 --> 01:01:32,105
What are you guys doing?

888
